 Release Name----- The.2010.Vancouver.Winter.Olympics.Closing.Cermony.HDTV.XviD-2HD
 Release Date----- 02/27/2010
 Release Size----- 1400Mb
 Source----------- HDTV
 Resolution------- 624x352
 Frame Rate------- 29.97

 NBC's coverage of the closing of the 2010 Vancouver Winter Olympics. As usual
 differs from other broadcast networks including a missing performer in the concert
 portion at the end (which NBC delayed til 11:30pm). Other things noticed, part of
 John Furlongs speech was cut as well as other minor differences to that of CTV
 including the strange inclusion of montages and a medal ceremony in the middle of 
 the event (as I assume there was some production delay, since CTV also took a long
 commercial break at that time).  If we can, we'll dust off a CTV recording for comparison.

 As a member and resident of the home country of Canada and host city of Vancouver. I 
 have never felt prouder to be a Canadian and as Neil Young so gracefully put it. "Long
 May You Run".

 Time permitting, we'll dust off a few more events before officially putting this Olympics
 to bed.
